1 (f) Establishing and maintaining a companion website section to inform
2 participating inmate's families, department partners, and community
3 supporters about the campus programs;
4 (g) Managing partnership components pertaining to the educational status of
5 participating inmates, including:
6 1. Initial college application completion and other educational records
7 required for admission;
8 2. Academic records and materials to determine transfer credit and
9 initial placement;
10 3. Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) completion and
11 submission, including eligibility criteria and financial aid payment
12 options;
13 4. Facilitation of financial aid payments for tuition, books, and supplies
14 on behalf of the participating inmate, ensuring no direct
15 disbursements to the inmate;
16 5. Orientation for participating inmates each term addressing:
17 a. College policies and procedures;
18 b. Program requirements;
19 c. FAFSA and payment plans;
20 d. Code of student conduct and college student expectations; and
21 e. Available support services;
22 6. Completion of graduation application and transfer enrollment if
23 desired;
24 7. Instructional materials that comply with the facility requirements of
25 the department; and
26 8. Quality assurance processes, including:
27 a. Course evaluations;
