2 Section 4. KRS 335B.020 is amended to read as follows:
3 (1) A[No] person shall not be disqualified from public employment[,] or[nor shall a
4 person be disqualified] from pursuing, practicing, or engaging in any occupation for
5 which a license is required solely because of a:
6 (a) Prior conviction of a crime, unless the crime for which the person was
7 convicted directly relates to the position of employment sought or the
8 occupation for which the license is sought; or
9 (b) Finding that an applicant lacks good character or fails to meet any other
10 similar standard where a criminal conviction is the sole basis for the
11 finding.
12 (2) In determining if a conviction directly relates to the position of public employment
13 sought or the occupation for which the license is sought, the hiring or licensing
14 authority shall consider the:
15 (a) [The ]Nature and seriousness of the crime for which the individual was
16 convicted and the passage of time since its commission;
17 (b) [The ]Relationship of the crime to the purposes of regulating the position of
18 public employment sought or the occupation for which the license is sought;
19 and
20 (c) [The ]Relationship of the crime to the ability, capacity, and fitness required to
21 perform the duties and discharge the responsibilities of the position of
22 employment or occupation.
23 (3) There shall be a rebuttable presumption for any occupational license that
24 requires good moral character that the person applying for the license is of good
25 moral character if, after the criminal conviction, the person obtains a certificate
26 of employability pursuant to Section 3 of this Act and the certificate has not been
27 revoked. This rebuttable presumption shall not apply if the conviction would
